      },
      tulip: {
        name: "Tulip",
        info: `Tulips are perennial flowers that bloom in the spring, famous for their vibrant colors and elegant shape. Originating from Central Asia, they were first cultivated in Turkey and later introduced to Europe in the 16th century. Tulips come in nearly every color of the rainbow, including red, pink, yellow, white, and purple. They are often associated with deep love, rebirth, and fresh beginnings. The tulip became a symbol of wealth during the 17th century Dutch ‚ÄúTulip Mania,‚Äù a period when the flowers were traded at extremely high prices. Tulips are simple yet striking, with their smooth, elongated petals and strong stems. They symbolize perfect love and are often used to express admiration in the language of flowers. They continue to be one of the most sought-after flowers for spring gardens.`
      },
      sunflower: {
        name: "Sunflower",
        info: `Sunflowers are iconic, bright yellow flowers that turn their faces toward the sun, a phenomenon known as heliotropism. These tall flowers are known for their large, round heads and vibrant color, symbolizing adoration, loyalty, and longevity. They are native to North America and have been cultivated for thousands of years, valued for their seeds and oil. Sunflower seeds are a popular snack, and sunflower oil is widely used in cooking. The flowers themselves are often seen as a symbol of positivity and happiness. Sunflowers are also used in art and photography, symbolizing hope and a bright future. They bloom in the summer and are a popular choice for gardeners looking to add a cheerful touch. Their association with the sun represents warmth, vitality, and energy.`
      },
      daisy: {
        name: "Daisy",
        info: `Daisies are cheerful, simple flowers that are often associated with innocence, purity, and fresh beginnings. They are part of the Asteraceae family and have a distinctive appearance, with white petals and a yellow center. The name ‚Äúdaisy‚Äù comes from the Old English term ‚Äúday's eye,‚Äù referring to the way the flower opens at sunrise and closes at sunset. Daisies are commonly found in wildflower meadows and gardens, growing in clusters. Their simple beauty and resilience make them a symbol of childhood, love, and loyalty. Daisies have also been used in herbal remedies for centuries, with extracts believed to help with inflammation. They are frequently given as gifts to symbolize purity and truth. The daisy‚Äôs ability to grow in a variety of conditions makes it a beloved and hardy flower.`
      },
      lily: {
        name: "Lily",
        info: `Lilies are elegant flowers that are often associated with purity, renewal, and fertility. They come in various colors, including white, pink, yellow, and orange, and each color has its own meaning. White lilies symbolize purity and virtue, while pink lilies represent abundance and prosperity. Lilies have been used in religious ceremonies, particularly in Christianity, where they represent the Virgin Mary. They also hold significant symbolism in various cultures, representing beauty, abundance, and transformation. Lilies are commonly used in weddings, funerals, and other important events due to their symbolic importance. Their graceful, trumpet-shaped flowers make them a favorite among florists and gardeners. The sweet fragrance of lilies is often used in perfumes.`
      },
      orchid: {
        name: "Orchid",
        info: `Orchids are a family of exotic, graceful flowers known for their intricate shapes and vibrant colors. They are one of the largest and most diverse plant families in the world, with thousands of species. Orchids symbolize love, beauty, strength, and fertility, and have been highly prized for their unique appearance. Ancient Greeks and Romans believed orchids had healing properties, and they are still used in traditional medicines today. Orchids are often associated with luxury and elegance, making them popular as ornamental flowers in homes and gardens. They thrive in tropical climates and require specific conditions to grow. Orchids have also been a part of cultural traditions, especially in Asia, where they represent wealth and refinement. Their rare and delicate beauty continues to captivate flower lovers around the world.`
      }
    };

    function searchFlower() {
      const query = document.getElementById('searchInput').value.toLowerCase();
      const result = document.getElementById('flowerResult');
      result.innerHTML = '';

      if (flowers[query]) {
        const flower = flowers[query];
        result.innerHTML = `
          <div class="flower">
            <div>
              <div class="flower-name">${flower.name}</div>
              <div class="flower-info">${flower.info}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        `;
      } else {
        result.innerHTML = '<p style="color: red; font-size: 20px;">Flower not found. Try rose, tulip, sunflower, daisy, lily, or orchid.</p>';
      }
    }
  </script>
